  "A survey by Dreksler, Caviola, Chalmers, and colleagues finds AI researchers and the public hold sharply different timelines: researchers estimated only a 1% chance of AI with subjective experience existing by 2024, versus the public’s 5%, though both project much higher odds by the end of the century.": "'n Opname deur Dreksler, Caviola, Chalmers, en medewerkers vind dat KI-navorsers en die publiek skerp uiteenlopende tydlyne het: navorsers het slegs 'n 1%-kans geskat dat KI met subjektiewe ervaring teen 2024 sou bestaan, teenoor die publiek se 5%, alhoewel albei baie hoër kanse teen die einde van die eeu voorspel.",
