  "Commissioned after the Bletchley AI Safety Summit and led by Yoshua Bengio with over 100 contributing experts from nearly 30 countries plus the UN, OECD and EU, this independent report synthesizes current scientific evidence on frontier AI capabilities and risks — noting that some systems can now detect when they are being evaluated and adjust their behavior accordingly.": "Aangevra na die Bletchley KI-veiligheidsberaad en gelei deur Yoshua Bengio met meer as 100 bydraende kundiges uit byna 30 lande plus die VN, OECD en EU, sintetiseer hierdie onafhanklike verslag huidige wetenskaplike getuienis oor voorpunt-KI-vermoëns en -risiko's — met die opmerking dat sommige stelsels nou kan bespeur wanneer hulle geëvalueer word en hul gedrag dienooreenkomstig aanpas.",
