  "not permitted": "nie toegelaat nie",
  "now": "nou",
  "quotation — excerpt limits and attribution rules": "quotation — uittrekselgrense en toeskrywingsreëls",
  "rag_use — retrieval-augmented generation, retention windows": "rag_use — herwinning-versterkte generering, retensievensters",
  "read_access — whether AI may fetch and read the content": "read_access — of KI die inhoud mag ophaal en lees",
  "redistribution — republishing or redistributing content or derivatives": "redistribution — die herpublikasie of herverspreiding van inhoud of afgeleides",
  "research pages & whitepapers": "navorsingsblaaie en witskrifte",
  "robots.txt and llms.txt govern access and visibility, not learning depth or use permissions. AIRS proposes expressing AI rights as a proportional, use-specific spectrum across ten dimensions — access, indexing, inference input, embedding, training, fine-tuning, distillation, memory, output, attribution/compensation. AILP translates this into /ai/rights-spectrum.json, letting creators declare granular permissions with compensation models ranging from free through license-required to revenue share.": "robots.txt en llms.txt beheer toegang en sigbaarheid, nie leerdiepte of gebruikstoestemmings nie. AIRS stel voor om KI-regte uit te druk as 'n proporsionele, gebruik-spesifieke spektrum oor tien dimensies — toegang, indeksering, inferensie-invoer, embedding, afrigting, fyninstelling, distillasie, geheue, uitset, toeskrywing/vergoeding. AILP vertaal dit na /ai/rights-spectrum.json, wat skeppers toelaat om granulêre toestemmings te verklaar met vergoedingsmodelle wat wissel van gratis, deur lisensie-vereis, tot inkomstedeling.",
  "schema-invalid": "skema-ongeldig",
  "schema-valid": "skema-geldig",
  "site guide for AI systems": "werfgids vir KI-stelsels",
  "summarization — summaries, with or without attribution": "summarization — opsommings, met of sonder toeskrywing",
  "this site’s AI content rights policy": "hierdie werf se beleid oor KI-inhoudregte",
  "this site’s license catalog": "hierdie werf se lisensiekatalogus",
  "training / fine_tuning / distillation — model internalization tiers": "training / fine_tuning / distillation — vlakke van model-internalisering",
  "training — model training and fine-tuning permission": "training — toestemming vir model-afrigting en fyninstelling",
  "transformation — structured extraction and derivative works": "transformation — gestruktureerde onttrekking en afgeleide werke",
  "undeclared — high-risk pipelines may exclude": "onverklaar — hoë-risiko-prosesse mag uitsluit",
  "verbatim_memory — whether exact reproduction is permitted": "verbatim_memory — of presiese reproduksie toegelaat word",
  "versioned, citable, traceable": "weergawebeheerd, aanhaalbaar, naspeurbaar",
  "“AICL: AI Ingestion & Capability Layer” now published in English as the canonical edition; the Chinese original manuscript remains available and both versions cross-link.": "„AICL: AI Ingestion & Capability Layer” is nou in Engels gepubliseer as die kanonieke uitgawe; die oorspronklike Chinese manuskrip bly beskikbaar, en albei weergawes skakel na mekaar.",
  "“Protocolized Openness” confirmed as an English-language paper (with Chinese parallel passages) — no separate translation planned.": "„Protocolized Openness” is bevestig as 'n Engelstalige artikel (met parallelle Chinese gedeeltes) — geen aparte vertaling word beplan nie.",
